        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 2:46PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 246 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Chappells Mill to Montrose to Magnolia, and
moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Dublin, Cochran, East Dublin, Chester, Dexter, Dudley, Cadwell,
Rentz, Montrose, Allentown, Dubois, Spann, Plainfield, Empire, Mobley
Crossing, Roddy, Nicklesville, Baileys Park, Rowland, and Minter.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
